SIMPLE: ihvh
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: IHVH
<hw>IHVH</hw>. <altsp>[Written also <asp>JHVH</asp>,
<asp>YHVH</asp>.]</altsp> <def>A transliteration of the four constants
forming the Hebrew tetragrammaton or ⟦ldquo⟧incommunicable name⟦rdquo⟧
of the Supreme Being, which in latter Jewish tradition is not pronounced
save with the vowels of <xex>adonai</xex> or <xex>elohim</xex>, so that
the true pronunciation is lost.</def></p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Numerous attempts have been made to represent the
supposed original form of the word, as Jahaveh, Jahvaj, Jahve, Jahveh,
Yahve, Yahveh, Yahwe, Yahweh, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ik</ent>⟦br⟧
